parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or fail to shift gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission fails to shift gears
the transmission warning light comes on
the vehicle jerks or hesitates when shifting gears

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the manual transmission or clutch can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or fail to shift gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: grinding or crunching sounds when shifting
clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
